@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.About.UI

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">About DotNetCloud</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud is a self-hosted, open-source cloud platform built with .NET — a modern alternative to NextCloud. It provides file storage, chat, calendar, contacts, notes, and more, all running on your own infrastructure.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Version Information</h2>
        <p>The version displayed on the About page is read from the running assembly at startup and reflects the exact build you are running. Check the <strong>Open-Source Components</strong> section for attributions and license information.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Getting Help</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Visit the project repository for documentation and issue tracking.</li>
            <li>Check the master project plan and implementation checklist in <code>docs/</code> for development status.</li>
            <li>Report bugs or request features on GitHub.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
